actr.model

Class Symbol

  • java.lang.Object
    • actr.model.Symbol

  • public class Symbol
extends java.lang.Object
    A symbol within the system, roughly represented as a string but allowing "==" as a fast test for equality.

    This class maintains a hash table associating strings to symbols. When a user accesses a symbol using the Symbol.get() methods (e.g., Symbol.get("hello") or Symbol.get(3.5)), the methods return the symbol from the hash table if it exists, or create and return a new symbol if it does not yet exist. Symbols can be compared for equality efficiently using the "==" operator (rather than performing a string comparison of the symbol names).

    The class also provides a large set of pervasive symbols for heavily used symbols within the ACT-R system (e.g., the names of buffers and buffer states). The variables are simply shorthand alternatives to the longer forms that use the Symbol.get() methods; for example, Symbol.isa is equivalent to Symbol.get("isa").

    Author:
    Dario Salvucci
